eligibility_criteria.description:
Minimum age: 40 Years
Maximum age: 60 Years
Participants may not have received prior EGFR inhibitors for any disease
History or current hepatitis or other liver disease

Prolonged QTc interval on pre-entry electrocardiogram; QTc must be of less than CTC grade 2 (=< 470 msec) using appropriate correction formula with manual read by investigator if required; the electrocardiogram (ECG) may be repeated for evaluation of eligibility after management of correctable causes for observed QTc prolongation

At least one prior treatment regimen but no more than 3 prior chemotherapy regimens; patients previously treated with monoclonal antibodies or radiotherapy to a single site will be eligible; these therapies will be considered prior treatment regimens but will not be considered as prior chemotherapy; tumor vaccines will not be counted as prior therapies, as all such agents are investigational
Eastern Cooperative Oncology Group (ECOG) performance status of 0-1

outcome_measures.measure: Change in presence/absence of immune suppression
outcome_measures.time_frame: Baseline to up to 6 months after the last immunization

outcome_measures.measure: Change in Eastern Cooperative Oncology Group (ECOG) Performance Status
outcome_measures.time_frame: Measured up to 2 years after the last subject has enrolled in the study.
